Il y a 10 jours je trouvais la force de t’envoyer un message afin de reprendre contact après 10 ans de silence. Tu m’as rappelé et nous avons passé 3h au téléphone à parler de l’amour, l’amour inconditionnel, l’amour fou, voué à l’échec, si puissant si douloureux. Nous avons partagé nos peines nos pleures nos doutes nos failles… comme à ton habitude tu as été d’une empathie folle, tu m’as écouté, tu m’as compris, tu m’as aidé. Et depuis 10 jours chaque matin je me réveillais avec un message de toi, quelques vers d’Aragon, ou juste une pensée chaleureuse qui me réchauffait le cœur comme un feu de bois. Puis cette nuit a 4h du matin je reçois un appel qui m’annonce que tu n’es plus. Que je ne pourrais plus te serrer dans mes bras, te dire encore à quel point tu as été essentielle à l’homme que je suis et à celui que je serais. En l’espace de 2 mois je perds la femme de ma vie et l’homme qui m’a tout appris tout donné. 
Alors je me raccroche comme un fou comme un acharné à la dernière phrase que tu m’aies dite mercredi. « Le vent se lève il faut tenter de vivre » 
Je t’aimerais à jamais 
Et j’honorerais ta mémoire en me battant et en profitant de chaque jours qu’il me reste à vivre. 
Repose en paix mon ami, mon frère, mon mentor.

Thomas Lavelle @thomaslavellephotography is a renowned photographer recognised for his captivating portraits among the likes of celebrities such as Kristen Stewart, Willem Dafoe, and Jennifer Connelly. His signature style involves high contrast images, with subjects often gazing directly into the camera. Lavelle’s talent lies in his attitude to capture the very essence of his subjects, allowing their innermost selves to shine through his lens. To him, the heart of photographic artistry lies in the skilful balance of opposing elements such as black and white, feminine and masculine, strong and soft.

During his formative teenage years, Lavelle immersed himself in the world of skateboarding, which sparked a deep affection for the surrounding environment. Furthermore, Lavelle’s upbringing in a creative household, with his father being a renowned architect known for his brutalist style, further nurtured his minimalism and contemporary artistic expressions. This is especially evident in his photos which capture the human form with elegance.

Lavelle’s work is among the likes of names such as Cannes Film Festival, @montblanc, @GQ, @aubadeparis, @thewoolmarkcompany, and many more.

It’s been years since I tell models I work with that I’m not looking for beauty but for attitude. 
When you work with me you don’t pose, you move, you play the character, you are the character. I create a space with my own artistic direction where they can express themselves. 

it is a moment of liberation and freedom. the images we create are created in pairs. I am not a puppeteer.

We explore together, we take risks together, we creat together.
